  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-xs-12 col-md-6">
      <div class="green-header">
        <h5><strong>The Old Bridge Inn</strong></h5>
      </div>
      <div class="white-card">
        <p><a href="http://www.oldbridgeinn.co.uk/" class="green-link", target="blank">The Old Bridge Inn</a> is a traditional country pub by the River Spey in Aviemore, with a fantastic locally-sourced menu and a huge whisky selection. They often have live music and dogs are allowed in front of the fire in the bar area.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="green-header">
        <h5><strong>La Taverna</strong></h5>
      </div>
      <div class="white-card">
        <p><a href="http://www.highrange.co.uk/taverna" class="green-link", target="blank">La Taverna</a> is a family-owned Italian Pizzeria with buffet in Aviemore. Perfect for the kids! Very popular with locals and visitors alike.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="green-header">
        <h5><strong>​The Druie</strong></h5>
      </div>
      <div class="white-card">
        <p><a href="http://rothiemurchus.net/food-drink/" class="green-link", target="blank">The Druie</a> is located on the Rothiemurchus Estate, serving great lunches with fish, venison and beef from the estate. Also great for coffee and home baking. Dogs are welcome in their outdoor seating area.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="green-header">
        <h5><strong>Carrbridge Kitchen</strong></h5>
      </div>
      <div class="white-card">
        <p>The Carrbridge Kitchen is a fantastic Scottish fusion restaurant serving delicious lunches, dinners, coffee and cake.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="green-header">
        <h5><strong>Muckrach Country House Hotel</strong></h5>
      </div>
      <div class="white-card">
        <p><a href="http://www.muckrach.com/" class="green-link", target="blank">Muckrach Lodge</a> is a stunning example of a Victorian shooting lodge that underwent a total renovation and now offers a stylish brasserie-style restaurant near Carrbridge which serves simple, stylish and delicious dishes made using local ingredients sourced from the Scottish Highlands.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="green-header">
        <h5><strong>The High St Merchants</strong></h5>
      </div>
      <div class="white-card">
        <p>This gem of a <a href="http://www.thehighstmerchants.com/" class="green-link", target="blank">cafe and gallery</a> in Grantown-on-Spey is a firm favourite with local and visitors alike. Pop in for a delicious scone, tasty lunch or pint of Two Thirsty Men beer (brewed right next door!). Also open for dinner on Friday and Saturday evenings.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="green-header">
        <h5><strong>The Sugar Bowl</strong></h5>
      </div>
      <div class="white-card">
        <p><a href="https://www.facebook.com/pg/sugarbowlkingussie/about/?ref=page_internal" class="green-link", target="blank">The Sugar Bowl</a> in Kingussie is a lovely little coffee shop which also sells some great gifts. Breakfast, lunch, drinks and coffee are served every day other than Monday.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-xs-12 col-md-6">
      <div class="green-header">
        <h5><strong>The Winking Owl</strong></h5>
      </div>
      <div class="white-card">
        <p><a href="http://thewinkingowl.co/" class="green-link", target="blank">The Winking Owl</a> is located in the centre of Aviemore. This lovely gastro pub is owned by the Cairngorm Brewery and has an impressive selection of real ales to sample.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="green-header">
        <h5><strong>Mountain Cafe</strong></h5>
      </div>
      <div class="white-card">
        <p>The <a href="http://mountaincafe-aviemore.co.uk/" class="green-link", target="blank">Mountain Cafe</a> in the centre of Aviemore is a must for a hearty breakfast and also great for lunch. This multi-award winning cafe has a selection of cakes like you've never seen before. Be prepared to queue for a table but it is worth the wait!</p>
      </div>
      <div class="green-header">
        <h5><strong>1896 Gallery and Coffee Shop</strong></h5>
      </div>
      <div class="white-card">
        <p><a href="https://www.facebook.com/1896GalleryAndCoffeeShop/" class="green-link", target="blank">1896</a> is a lovely family-run coffee shop in Boat of Garten. They serve delicious soup and scones as well as a good selection of home baking.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="green-header">
        <h5><strong>​Andersons</strong></h5>
      </div>
      <div class="white-card">
        <p><a href="http://www.andersonsrestaurant.co.uk/" class="green-link", target="blank">Andersons</a> is a relaxed and informal bistro style restaurant in Boat of Garten. It's a great choice for some good home-cooked Scottish cuisine. It is recommended by Nick Nairn!</p>
      </div>
      <div class="green-header">
        <h5><strong>The Cross</strong></h5>
      </div>
      <div class="white-card">
        <p><a href="http://thecross.co.uk/" class="green-link", target="blank">The Cross</a> is a smart restaurant in Kingussie, the perfect setting to celebrate a special occasion or simply to enjoy some deliciously prepared local produce.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="green-header">
        <h5><strong>​The Wild Flour</strong></h5>
      </div>
      <div class="white-card">
        <p>The Wild Flour is a lovely wee cafe in Newtonmore that serves homemade treats in a relaxed atmosphere.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="green-header">
        <h5><strong>​​The Craigellachie Speyside</strong></h5>
      </div>
      <div class="white-card">
        <p>A 40-minute drive north on the A95 from Nethy Bridge, this stylish small <a href="http://www.craigellachiehotel.co.uk/" class="green-link", target="blank">hotel</a> is the perfect spot for a relaxed lunch or dinner. The Copper Dog pub downstairs serves quality local fare, with live music on summer evenings, and the Quaich bar is home to more than 900 whiskies!</p>
      </div>
      <div class="green-header">
        <h5><strong>​Nethy House</strong></h5>
      </div>
      <div class="white-card">
        <p>A delightful little cafe with home cooked food and fantastic coffee in the heart of Nethy Bridge.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
