      <div class="green-header">
        <h5><strong>Mambos</strong></h5>
      </div>
      <div class="white-card">
        <p>Mambos is the place to be on a Saturday night in Aviemore. This is a lively bar with music and dancing until the wee hours.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="green-header">
        <h5><strong>​Cairngorm Hotel</strong></h5>
      </div>
      <div class="white-card">
        <p><a href="http://www.cairngorm.com/restaurant-bar/" class="green-link", target="blank">The Cairngorm Hotel</a> is a traditional hotel pub, very popular with locals and holiday-makers. Live music is often heard here, they also support many local events.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="green-header">
        <h5><strong>The Cairn Hotel</strong></h5>
      </div>
      <div class="white-card">
        <p>At <a href="http://www.cairnhotel.co.uk/" class="green-link", target="blank">The Cairn Hotel</a> in Carrbridge, you can enjoy a country pub atmosphere with a real log fire on a chilly day or outdoor seating on a sunny day. They serve great pub lunches and suppers, always with some friendly banter and maybe some real ale or a wee dram.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-xs-12 col-md-6">
      <div class="green-header">
        <h5><strong>The Old Bridge Inn</strong></h5>
      </div>
      <div class="white-card">
        <p><a href="http://www.oldbridgeinn.co.uk/" class="green-link", target="blank">The Old Bridge Inn</a> is a traditional country pub with a great selection of beers, whiskies and other beverages. A cosy, comfy and popular pub which on occasion throws a great party with live folk/pop music.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="green-header">
        <h5><strong>Doo Below</strong></h5>
      </div>
      <div class="white-card">
        <p>An apres ski bar in the heart of Aviemore that's fun in all seasons. Popular with locals and holiday makers.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="green-header">
        <h5><strong>​​The Grant Arms Hotel</strong></h5>
      </div>
      <div class="white-card">
        <p>You will find <a href="http://www.grantarmshotel.com/" class="green-link", target="blank">The Grant Arms Hotel</a> in the heart of Grantown. They offer draught beers as well as locally brewed guest ales and they have a great selection of Speyside single malts.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-xs-12">
      <div class="text-line before grey text-center">
        <h3>Play</h3>
      </div>
      <br>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-xs-12 col-md-6">
      <div class="green-header">
        <h5><strong>Anagach Woods</strong></h5>
      </div>
      <div class="white-card">
        <p>There are several lovely paths and tracks throughout <a href="http://www.anagachwoods.org.uk/" class="green-link", target="blank">Anagach Woods</a>, a beautiful pine forest in Grantown on Spey, great for walking and biking, popular for dog walking and perfect for a family picnic.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="green-header">
        <h5><strong>​Cairngorm Mountain</strong></h5>
      </div>
      <div class="white-card">
        <p><a href="http://www.cairngormmountain.org/" class="green-link", target="blank">Cairngorm Mountain</a> is Britains premier ski destination, funicular railway and Britain's highest restaurant. Perfect for snow sports, biking, walking, climbing and only 14 km from Aviemore. Kids love the ride on the funicular.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="green-header">
        <h5><strong>Landmark Forest Adventure Park</strong></h5>
      </div>
      <div class="white-card">
        <p><a href="http://www.landmarkpark.co.uk/" class="green-link", target="blank">Landmark</a> in Carrbridge is fun for all the family offering everything from a roller coaster, high ropes, indoor and outdoor play areas to a new butterfly enclosure. They are event rides and attractions specically for toddlers.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="green-header">
        <h5><strong>Rothiemurchus Estate</strong></h5>
      </div>
      <div class="white-card">
        <p>A wide range of activities are on offer at the <a href="http://rothiemurchus.net/" class="green-link", target="blank">Rothiemurchus Estate</a>, including fishing, land rover tours, high ropes, shooting and gorge walking. The Visitor Centre will be able to give you all of the information and make all of the bookings that you need. Babies and toddlers really enjoy feeding the fish at the fishery and visiting all of the animals around the estate.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="green-header">
        <h5><strong>Loch Insh Outdoor Centre</strong></h5>
      </div>
      <div class="white-card">
        <p>A fantastic selection of water sports on <a href="http://www.lochinsh.com/" class="green-link", target="blank">Loch Insh</a> including lessons and full activity holidays. There are also two great play parks there for the little ones and lots of fun watching the ducks on the loch.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="green-header">
        <h5><strong>Highland Folk Museum</strong></h5>
      </div>
      <div class="white-card">
        <p>Have a wander back through the way we used to live at the <a href="https://www.highlifehighland.com/highlandfolkmuseum/" class="green-link", target="blank">Highland Folk Museum</a>. Perfect for kids of all ages. Educational and lots of fun. There is a great play park for the little ones here too.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="green-header">
        <h5><strong>Highland Wildlife Park</strong></h5>
      </div>
      <div class="white-card">
        <p>The <a href="http://www.highlandwildlifepark.org.uk/" class="green-link", target="blank">Highland Wildlife Park</a> is home to a huge selection of animals from sub-arctic climates including 3 polar bears and a wolf pack! You can enjoy a walk around the enclosures then get up close and personal with a drive around the safari park.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="green-header">
        <h5><strong>Craggan Outdoors</strong></h5>
      </div>
      <div class="white-card">
        <p>​<a href="http://www.cragganoutdoors.co.uk/" class="green-link", target="blank">Craggan Outdoors</a> offers a large variety of outdoor activities specialising in organised group activities including gorge walking, golf, shooting, high wires and team building activities.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="green-header">
        <h5><strong>Ballindalloch Castle</strong></h5>
      </div>
      <div class="white-card">
        <p>Open to the public from Easter to the end of September, <a href="http://www.ballindallochcastle.co.uk/" class="green-link", target="blank">Ballindalloch Castle</a> has all you need for a lovely family day out. Just a 30-minute drive north of Nethy Bridge, there you will find llamas, donkeys, a children’s playground complete with many ride-on tractors, a grass labyrinth, beautiful gardens perfect for hide-and-seek, a great cafe and even its own golf course!</p>
      </div>
      <div class="green-header">
        <h5><strong>Shinty</strong></h5>
      </div>
      <div class="white-card">
        <p>Shinty (or Camanachd in Gaelic) is played regularly at <a href="http://www.newtonmoreshinty.com/" class="green-link", target="blank">Newtonmore</a> and <a href="https://www.facebook.com/Kingussie-Camanachd-Club-468484826551863/" class="green-link", target="blank">Kingussie</a>. Games are held regularly on weekday evenings or at weekends and all spectators warmly welcome! It’s a fast paced and thrilling traditional Highland sport and is a huge part of the Highland culture particularly in these two villages, who are fierce shinty rivals! See their websites/facebook pages for match details.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-xs-12 col-md-6">
      <div class="green-header">
        <h5><strong>Golf</strong></h5>
      </div>
      <div class="white-card">
        <p>Aviemore and the surrounding area is perfect for golfers with a huge selection of courses to choose from for all abilities. From the beautiful <a href="https://www.boatgolf.com/cms/" class="green-link", target="blank">Boat of Garten</a>, <a href="http://www.abernethygolfclub.com/" class="green-link", target="blank">Abernethy</a> and <a href="http://www.carrbridgegolf.co.uk/" class="green-link", target="blank">Carrbridge</a> courses to the impressive 18 hole <a href="http://www.macdonaldhotels.co.uk/our-hotels/macdonald-aviemore-resort/golf/" class="green-link", target="blank">Spey Valley Championship Course</a> now in the top 100 of UK golf courses.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="green-header">
        <h5><strong>Clan warfare</strong></h5>
      </div>
      <div class="white-card">
        <p><a href="http://www.aviemorepaintball.com/" class="green-link", target="blank">Paint-balling</a> in the heart of Scotland's ancient pine forest.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="green-header">
        <h5><strong>​​Full On Adventure</strong></h5>
      </div>
      <div class="white-card">
        <p><a href="http://www.fullonadventure.co.uk/" class="green-link", target="blank">Full On Adventure</a> offers extreme adventure on the River Spey during the summer months, from paddle boarding and kayak touring to river tubing down the Spey!</p>
      </div>
      <div class="green-header">
        <h5><strong>​​G2 Outdoors</strong></h5>
      </div>
      <div class="white-card">
        <p><a href="http://www.g2outdoor.co.uk/" class="green-link", target="blank">G2 Outdoors</a> offer thrill seeking adventure for all ages and abilities. From ski touring in the winter to white water rafting and gorge walking in the warmer months. G2 also run a zip park with over 2 km of lines zipping through the ancient forest.</p>
      </div>
